          </mml:mfenced>
        </mml:math>
      </disp-formula>
      <p>where <italic>t</italic> = each timepoint, and <italic>f(t<sub>i</sub>)</italic> = density level for each timepoint <italic>i</italic>, equivalent to <italic>y<sub>(t)</sub></italic>, and taken as the density level assigned by the DL model (range 1–6). Lastly, a pharmacodynamics Hill function (<xref rid="ref17" ref-type="bibr">Regoes et al., 2004</xref>) was adapted to express, for each antibiotic, the change in AUC as a function of the antibiotic concentration:</p>
